Over the last few decades, a huge resurgence in the interest and use of medicinal aromatic plant products has been witnessed (
Briskin, 2000
; 
Ncube et al., 2012
). Several plant-based compounds are recognized to play important preventive role against some chronic and degenerative diseases (e.g. cancer, cardiovascular and neurodegenerative disorders) and new scientific evidence is available demonstrating wide range of pharmacological and nutraceutical activities of plant natural products as pure molecules or herbal extracts (
Siddhuraju and Becker, 2007
; 
Fan et al., 2007
; 
Liu et al., 2008
). These include antioxidant, anticancer, and anti-inflammatory activities.

